1
00:00:32,041 --> 00:00:33,625
Wait! What if
someone sees us?

2
00:00:33,708 --> 00:00:34,791
You have to stop that.

3
00:00:34,875 --> 00:00:36,833
Please, stop!

4
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:38,958
Basically, Harutora
started living in the dorms

5
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:41,333
with Touji so Natsume
decided to move in there, too,

6
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:42,708
so they could be
closer together!

7
00:00:42,791 --> 00:00:44,500
The situation has
turned into a passionate,

8
00:00:44,583 --> 00:00:46,833
heart-pounding love triangle,
and I can't get enough!

9
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:47,916
Isn't it exciting?

10
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,416
I can't take it;
how will this thing end?

11
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,125
You know, if you're
going to be a dorm mother,

12
00:00:51,208 --> 00:00:52,958
the boys' dorm
is the way to go!

13
00:00:53,041 --> 00:00:55,666
Come on. That can't
be, like, for real.

14
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:57,333
Making things up again, Mako?

15
00:00:57,416 --> 00:00:58,791
[FUJINO]
I'm completely serious!

16
00:00:58,875 --> 00:01:00,916
Right now, the boys' dorm
is like a real-life fantasy,

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:01,916
and I love it!

18
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,625
They're the best show ever!

19
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:06,166
Anything could
happen at this point.

20
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:07,541
[KIFU] Hm?

21
00:01:09,791 --> 00:01:12,125
[FUJINO and KIFU] A-Ah!

22
00:01:12,208 --> 00:01:13,583
[HARUTORA]
Stop moving around!

23
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:17,416
C'mon! Can we at least get
out of the freakin' hallway?

24
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,958
Did I not say
it was a fantasy?

25
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:20,541
This is so scandalous!

26
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:22,791
No! No pictures; this
isn't what it looks like!

27
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:25,125
Yeah. Sure, whatever you say.

28
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:27,500
I'm Ako, the dorm mother
for the girls' dorm.

29
00:01:27,583 --> 00:01:29,583
It's great to finally
meet you, Harutora.

30
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:32,125
I've heard so many stories
about you from Mako.

31
00:01:32,208 --> 00:01:33,791
So, so, many stories!

32
00:01:33,875 --> 00:01:36,666
[HARUTORA] Maybe introduce
yourself before going paparazzi!

33
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:38,875
And delete the pictures
you already took!

34
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:40,000
What's with
the racket?

35
00:01:40,083 --> 00:01:41,125
For real!

36
00:01:41,208 --> 00:01:43,625
[HARUTORA] U-Uhh...

37
00:01:43,708 --> 00:01:45,166
[FEMALE STUDENTS] Ahhhh!

38
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:46,708
[FEMALE STUDENT 6A]
OMG, wait till the other girls

39
00:01:46,791 --> 00:01:48,083
hear about this!

40
00:01:48,166 --> 00:01:51,291
[HARUTORA] Hey, wait.
It's not like that!

41
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:52,875
Ohh...

42
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:25,041
[TOUJI] Let me
get this straight;

43
00:03:25,125 --> 00:03:27,125
Natsume made a familiar to
use the public bathrooms,

44
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:28,458
but it malfunctioned.

45
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:30,333
Harutora caught it,
but other people showed up

46
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:32,208
and saw you in a rather
compromising situation?

47
00:03:32,291 --> 00:03:34,625
[HARUTORA] Mm-hmm.

48
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:35,916
Well, that explains a lot.

49
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,708
I was wondering why
everyone's acting like

50
00:03:37,791 --> 00:03:39,291
our table had the plague.

51
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:40,916
[BOYS chatter]

52
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,791
[HARUTORA sighs]

53
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:45,291
This is so humiliating.

54
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:46,708
[footsteps]
[HARUTORA] Hm?

55
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:48,791
[FUJINO hums]

56
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:50,166
[inaudible]

57
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:51,541
[FUJINO whispers]
Don't worry!

58
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:53,750
[FUJINO giggles]

59
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:55,916
Oh, perfect, I bet
she's including me

60
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,250
in her twisted
little fantasy.

61
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,333
Probably.

62
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:01,000
Man. Well, now this
isn't funny anymore.

63
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:02,458
Look, you're playing
with fire here.

64
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:03,875
Dressing like
a guy's one thing,

65
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,125
but living in a boys'
dorm is too much.

66
00:04:06,208 --> 00:04:07,875
Whatever; the plan
itself was perfect.

67
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,041
I just needed
someone to see me.

68
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,333
No one would
doubt I was a boy

69
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:13,416
if that familiar had
been seen without clothes.

70
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,000
I guess technically
your plan worked,

71
00:04:15,083 --> 00:04:16,583
so congrats on that.

72
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:18,250
[KON] How inappropriate.

73
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:20,166
No one asked you, Kon!

74
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:22,625
You shouldn't butt in when
you haven't been summoned!

75
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,125
U-Um...

76
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,750
Anyway, we can't
change what happened.

77
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,291
We'll just have to try to
forget the whole thing.

78
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:31,333
[HARUTORA]
She's full of it.

79
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:33,750
[TOUJI]
Totally full of it.

80
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:35,791
[TOUJI] Shopping?
Tomorrow?

81
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:37,125
[HARUTORA] Yeah.

82
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,375
All I've done since I got
here is freaking study.

83
00:04:39,458 --> 00:04:40,916
[NATSUME]
And even then,

84
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,958
you still haven't been able
to keep up with classwork.

85
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:45,958
I don't care!
I just need a break!

86
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:48,166
I can't take it anymore!
Ever since I left home,

87
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,666
all I've done is go
back and forth between

88
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:52,166
dorm and school, dorm and
school, dorm and school!

89
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,666
[NATSUME] So that's
what this is about.

90
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,166
You know, it's okay
to relax a little

91
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:56,583
every once in a while!

92
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:58,875
Sorry, dude. I already
have plans tomorrow.

93
00:04:58,958 --> 00:05:00,250
How do you
have plans?

94
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:01,833
Why don't you
two go together?

95
00:05:01,916 --> 00:05:03,291
It'll be fun.

96
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,416
Guess we might as well.

97
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,916
How about it, Natsume?
Shopping tomorrow?

98
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,791
You mean like a--

99
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:12,875
[HARUTORA] Huh?

100
00:05:12,958 --> 00:05:16,291
[NATSUME] A date?

101
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:17,333
[HARUTORA]
What's wrong?

102
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,666
You're face is
getting really red.

103
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,666
[NATSUME]
No, it's not. I'm fine.

104
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,291
I'm gonna die.

105
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,416
I can't handle
all this suspense.

106
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:29,416
[CROWD chatters]

107
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,875
Dude. What's
wrong with you?

108
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,583
You're wearing your uniform?

109
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:34,625
Yeah, so what.

110
00:05:34,708 --> 00:05:36,208
I don't have any
other boys' clothes.

111
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:37,208
[HARUTORA] Really?

112
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:39,083
What have you been
doing until now?

113
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:41,708
[NATSUME] All I've needed so
far was this and some sweats.

114
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:43,083
The only places I ever go

115
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:45,375
are the convenience store
and the mall anyway.

116
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:47,375
Wow. That's kinda pathetic.

117
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:49,541
You, of all people,
are calling me pathetic?

118
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:50,916
Calm, down.

119
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,916
Don't worry; we can get
you some clothes today, too.

120
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,875
[NATSUME] I don't
need your help, okay?

121
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:58,375
Yes, you do; someone's
gotta tell you what's cool.

122
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,875
This is so embarrassing.

123
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:03,375
[HARUTORA] Whoa.
There are so many people here!

124
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:05,250
As expected of "Ya-Shibu."

125
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,291
What? Ya-Shibu?

126
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,250
Why are you saying
Shibuya like that?

127
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:11,375
Because it's not at all
pronounced that way.

128
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:13,166
But Touji said
the slang is to say

129
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:15,750
the last part of a place
before the rest of the word.

130
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,250
Za-Gin! Gi-Roppon!

131
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:20,500
Sorry, probably
one of his tricks.

132
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:21,500
Seriously?

133
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,250
No wonder Kyoko said that.

134
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:26,083
Oh, Tenma had a weird
look on his face, too.

135
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:27,791
No one else around
you was doing it;

136
00:06:27,875 --> 00:06:29,375
why didn't that clue you in?

137
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:30,458
[HARUTORA] Wait.

138
00:06:30,541 --> 00:06:32,083
There was somebody
doing it, though.

139
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,916
Really?
Well, who was it?

140
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,500
Mister Ohtomo.

141
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:39,041
[OHTOMO] Ya-Shibu.
Juku-Shin.

142
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:41,875
Bukuro-Ike.

143
00:06:41,958 --> 00:06:44,125
Gawa-Shina...

144
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,375
[HARUTORA] Oh god.

145
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:47,375
Why did I believe him?

146
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,250
[NATSUME chuckles]

147
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,666
You know what?

148
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:52,916
It's been a while since we've
hung out like this, huh?

149
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,166
Like, just the two
of us by ourselves.

150
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,125
[HARUTORA]
Oh yeah, it has been.

151
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,041
Not since we were kids, right?

152
00:06:59,125 --> 00:07:00,625
It hasn't been that long!

153
00:07:00,708 --> 00:07:03,916
Before Touji came, we went to
the fireworks festival together.

154
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,666
Fireworks festival?
We did?

155
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:08,125
Uh--No! Never mind!

156
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,625
You are so right; it's totally
been since we were kids;

157
00:07:10,708 --> 00:07:12,333
I was thinking of someone else.

158
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:14,833
Heh, heh!
Oh, silly me.

159
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:17,875
[HARUTORA]
Hm. Hey, wait up.

160
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:19,291
[NATSUME]
So what's the plan?

161
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,708
Where do you want
to go shopping?

162
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:22,583
[HARUTORA] I'd like to
check out second-hand stores.

163
00:07:22,666 --> 00:07:24,083
That's all I can afford,

164
00:07:24,166 --> 00:07:26,250
but it kinda feels good
just to get outside

165
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,583
and walk around a little while.

166
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:30,083
That's true.
This is pretty nice.

167
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:33,000
And it totally feels
like we're on a date!

168
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,666
[HARUTORA] So clothes
first, right?

169
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,708
You can be in charge of
deciding where we're gonna go.

170
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:39,208
In charge? Like, how?

171
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:40,458
I'm new here.

172
00:07:40,541 --> 00:07:42,000
I don't know where the
second-hand stores are.

173
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:44,750
Just guide us to
the general area.

174
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,291
There's no way! I can't!

175
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:49,458
The only place I've ever bought
clothes before is online.

176
00:07:49,541 --> 00:07:51,083
You mean girls'
clothes, too?

177
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:52,583
I just don't like
how at the store

178
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:54,583
all the people that
work there talk to you.

179
00:07:54,666 --> 00:07:56,375
Wait, seriously?

180
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:58,375
Well, I can go ask
someone for help.

181
00:07:58,458 --> 00:07:59,750
No, it's fine!

182
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:02,500
Why don't we just look
around on our own for a bit?

183
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:07,791
Wow, I guess I should've
waited for Touji after all.

184
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:10,708
[NATSUME] You're the one
that invited me, Harutora!

185
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:13,666
A proper escort would have
looked up places to go first!

186
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:14,958
And it's not my
fault you don't know

187
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:17,250
how to plan something
ahead of time!

188
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:18,500
Why are you upset?

189
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:21,625
What? I'm not upset
in the least, you dummy!

190
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:22,916
Uh. "You dummy"?

191
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,500
What are you, in the
first grade or something?

192
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:27,000
[NATSUME] Don't you dare
talk to me like that!

193
00:08:27,083 --> 00:08:29,250
Don't forget,
you're my familiar.

194
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:30,250
I see.

195
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:31,666
So even though
I'm new to the city,

196
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:35,291
I should navigate for my master
who never goes outside.

197
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:38,625
[NATSUME] Fine. I'll take
you to your stupid store!

198
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:43,291
[HARUTORA] Hey!

199
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:45,750
They don't sell second-hand
stuff in a department store!

200
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:51,583
Oh, come on.
It's almost three o'clock.

201
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:53,125
I'm starving.

202
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,500
[NATSUME]
Clothes first, right?

203
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:56,791
We can eat lunch after that.

204
00:08:56,875 --> 00:09:00,208
Aw. There goes my
precious Sunday.

205
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:04,291
[HARUTORA] No, wait.

206
00:09:04,375 --> 00:09:06,375
I didn't mean it
like that, Natsume!

207
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:09,791
[HARUTORA] Huh?

208
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:14,333
Natsume! Stop!

209
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:16,958
Don't touch me, Harutora!
I'm not ready to give up!

210
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:18,916
That's not it!
We shouldn't be here!

211
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,583
Whaddaya mean
"shouldn't be here"?

212
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,208
I mean, look around!

213
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,583
[NATSUME] Huh?

214
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:30,833
[NATSUME gasps]

215
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:32,333
Those are love hotels.

216
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:33,250
Oh no.

217
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,666
I'm shocked you
know about 'em.

218
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:35,833
Come here often?

219
00:09:35,916 --> 00:09:39,208
I didn't-- That's not what--

220
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,208
This is not what
I was planning.

221
00:09:41,291 --> 00:09:44,583
Yeah, of course not.
Just chill a bit, okay?

222
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,416
[NATSUME] Why?

223
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,375
Why what? Natsume?

224
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:49,916
Why did this happen?

225
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:55,875
We finally got to
go out together.

226
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:58,791
This is--This is awful.

227
00:09:58,875 --> 00:10:02,125
[NATSUME cries]

228
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:05,125
And my luck strikes,
yet again.

229
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,250
Hey, don't cry.

230
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,250
I'm not crying, you dummy.

231
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,333
[HARUTORA sighs]

232
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:12,708
We need to go;

233
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,708
we can't risk anyone seeing
us in an area like this.

234
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:16,250
[FUJINO]
Ako, you spot 'em anywhere?

235
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,291
[HARUTORA gasps]

236
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:18,416
[KIFU] No, I haven't
seen anything.

237
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,875
Are you positive you did?

238
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:22,583
Like, Natsume and Harutora
were actually together?

239
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:25,291
Yeah. I swear it.
I saw them!

240
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,541
Those two are gonna
go all the way tonight!

241
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:29,750
As their dorm room mother,
I have to stop them, right?

242
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,125
[KIFU] Mm-hm.

243
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:32,541
I love it!

244
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:35,333
[HARUTORA] Crap.
Where should we go?

245
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:39,541
[FUJINO] This is so going
in my journal tonight!

246
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:41,541
[KIFU] Did you
bring the camera?

247
00:10:41,625 --> 00:10:45,666
[FUJINO and KIFU 
chatter indistinctly]

248
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,166
What's a girl gotta
do to catch some

