Aahh!

494
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:35,166
[OHTOMO] Someone worked hard
on their day off, didn't they?

495
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,791
Who are you?

496
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:40,291
[MAGIC INVESTIGATOR 4A]
I can't move.

497
00:19:40,375 --> 00:19:42,916
It's an immobilizing spell.

498
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,458
[OHTOMO] The quality
of investigators

499
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:48,666
has really gone downhill.

500
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:51,333
Then again, perhaps this
just means that the mages

501
00:19:51,416 --> 00:19:54,250
in the Exorcism Bureau are that
much better, don't you think?

502
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,583
[MIYO] Working overtime,
Mister Ohtomo?

503
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:57,791
[OHTOMO]
Well, hello there.

504
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:59,541
I take it this
isn't news to you?

505
00:19:59,625 --> 00:20:02,541
[MIYO] I try to stay informed
when it comes to my students.

506
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:04,500
Seems to me you took a
rather significant risk

507
00:20:04,583 --> 00:20:06,583
with our charges, Principal.

508
00:20:06,666 --> 00:20:08,791
Why leave this idiot alone
even though you knew

509
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:12,500
a long time ago he was
actually a Yakou devotee?

510
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,291
[MIYO] We had confirmed
his connection to

511
00:20:14,375 --> 00:20:17,166
the Twin Horn Syndicate
before the incident.

512
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:20,583
Unfortunately, we did
not know anything else.

513
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:21,958
By any chance,
do you think you can

514
00:20:22,041 --> 00:20:24,208
wrangle me some
holiday pay for this?

515
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:26,750
[MIYO] Oh, but it's
for our dear students.

516
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:29,958
Surely money isn't
an issue to you.

517
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:34,166
Money is always an issue,
but I suppose it hardly matters.

518
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,916
If it goes down like
we think it will,

519
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:39,500
a little overtime won't
exactly make a difference.

520
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:41,041
Now we just wait to
see if they bother

521
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:43,625
showing their hand
for this moron.

522
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:46,541
[DOMAN]
So, he's been found out?

523
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:48,708
No matter; that
fool investigator

524
00:20:48,791 --> 00:20:51,125
was a constant
disappointment anyway.

525
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,166
[KAKUGYOUKI] I just wish you'd
stop having to use my name

526
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:54,791
in order to scare everyone.

527
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:58,041
So now what?
Take it easy for a while?

528
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:00,333
You're not concerned
about our cover?

529
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:03,166
Nah, it's not something I'd go
through the trouble to confirm.

530
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:06,041
I'm not much like
Hishamaru in that way.

531
00:21:06,125 --> 00:21:08,750
[DOMAN] Hmph. Sometimes I think
you're too indifferent

532
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,916
about your own ogre spirit.

533
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:14,625
Thanks to you, I was
spotted by that young one.

534
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:16,041
[KAKUGYOUKI]
Oh yeah, right, him.

535
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:18,375
He seems like he comes
from some decent stock.

536
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:19,958
I take it you know him?

537
00:21:20,041 --> 00:21:22,250
[DOMAN]
We did meet once.

538
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,041
He was extraordinarily impudent

539
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:27,125
and somehow managed
to escape my grasp.

540
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:29,708
But it cost him a leg
in the process.

541
00:21:29,791 --> 00:21:31,958
He sounds
interesting to me.

542
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,416
But, either way,

543
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,625
the head of Onmyo Prep is
a pretty capable astrologer.

544
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:38,500
Aren't you a little concerned
she may have already

545
00:21:38,583 --> 00:21:40,000
seen through your plans?

546
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:43,125
Oh, half the fun lies in
trying to outwit that old woman.

547
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:44,416
Yeah, well I have
no comment

548
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,291
when it comes to
your nasty hobbies.

549
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:48,166
That's really all I wanted.

550
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:50,125
Oh, wait, one more thing.

551
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:51,875
[DOMAN] Hm?

552
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:54,041
Do we know what
that kid is, yet?

553
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:56,208
[DOMAN] Only that he's
from a branch family.

554
00:21:56,291 --> 00:21:59,166
The dragon and tiger
have both appeared.

555
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,583
I have to say,

556
00:22:00,666 --> 00:22:02,875
that poor tiger is still
looking pretty shabby, though.

557
00:22:02,958 --> 00:22:05,541
Why do you ask; did he
do something interesting?

558
00:22:05,625 --> 00:22:07,125
[KAKUGYOUKI] No, not really.

559
00:22:07,208 --> 00:22:09,916
Nothing you need
to mess with anyway.

560
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,166
[DOMAN]
Now, now, my friend.

561
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:13,291
Did you not just tell
me you had no comment

562
00:22:13,375 --> 00:22:16,125
when it came to
my nasty hobbies?

563
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:20,833
[KAKUGYOUKI] You haven't
changed one bit.

564
00:22:27,125 --> 00:22:29,583
[inaudible]

565
00:22:29,666 --> 00:22:32,416
[KAKUGYOUKI]
You always were focused.

566
00:24:06,458 --> 00:24:08,958
[FUJINO]
It's a real-life fantasy!

567
00:24:09,041 --> 00:24:10,541
[KIFU] Romance!

568
00:24:10,625 --> 00:24:10,958
[FUJINO] Scandal!

